# WCL token cache + generated artifacts
.wcl-token.json
schema.json
reports/
# Fetched report data is ignored by default (an ad-hoc analysis of any report drops a folder here and
# shouldn't be committed) — EXCEPT the pinned benchmark pair that /startup uses. Committing just those
# two reports' data gives a fresh clone / new worktree / cloud session a WARM cache: /startup reads them
# off disk (cached_for passes, world-best is within its TTL) instead of cold-fetching ~520 points from
# the API. Keep this allow-list in sync with OURS_URL/THEIRS_URL in scripts/cloud_startup.py.
data/*
!data/pkHqfrBbhQK9GP1a/
!data/BxZPrhXYDfL1VKm8/
!data/pkHqfrBbhQK9GP1a-parses.json
!data/BxZPrhXYDfL1VKm8-parses.json
